1
00:00:23,080 --> 00:00:25,200
Even a living Buddha

2
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,640
wouldn't tutor me for no reason.

3
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:29,320
Sigh.

4
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:45,280
Could he have found out?

5
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,040
Why does he look a bit familiar?

6
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:56,000
Our key project is set up in Xihai City this time

7
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,360
because the supporting facilities here are complete.

8
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,360
Did you notice?

9
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:01,320
The head of this group is so young.

10
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:03,600
He's probably the son of a top executive.

11
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,459
Do you like him?

12
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:05,000
No.

13
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,520
People like that aren't in the same world as us.

14
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:08,920
With a large group like this taking the lead,

15
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:11,650
I guess there will be an investment boom in Xihai.

16
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:16,680
Why is he studying here too?

17
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:40,520
Were you staring at me in the hallway just now?

18
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,160
Me?

19
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,560
No, I wasn't.

20
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:44,280
The plants.

21
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:46,640
I wanted to see if the plants had been watered.

22
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,700
I'll go take a look.

23
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,690
I thought you needed me for something.

24
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:56,020
I do have something to ask of you, Senior.

25
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,759
Could you help tutor me?

26
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,000
Tutor you?

27
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:01,920
Yeah.

28
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,520
Please, Senior.

29
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,680
Oh, I see.

30
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,539
So how much are you going to pay for the tutoring?

31
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:11,320
Can we exchange it for something else, Senior?

32
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:13,160
Your Ans Group is so rich.

33
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:13,880
How could I afford it?

34
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:14,680
Wait a minute.

35
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,079
What did you just say?

36
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,079
Can I exchange it for something else?

37
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:19,640
No.

38
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,840
Your Ans Group is so rich.

39
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,840
Where did you hear that from?

40
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,520
Ans Group.

41
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,360
Is that a secret?

42
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,400
Yin Zixi,

43
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,850
take your materials

44
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:37,360
and find me in the broadcasting room later.

45
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,200
How does he know my name?

46
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,040
Are you sure you're not returning to the Student Council?

47
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,120
If I could,

48
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,360
I wouldn't even return to school.

49
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:02,960
Ugh.

50
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,240
This corporate debt

51
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,440
is an adult's matter.

52
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,560
Your father had you come back to school

53
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,240
for a good reason, of course.

54
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:12,720
Sir.

55
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:15,280
If your family were about to go bankrupt,

56
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,600
would you still be in the mood to study?

57
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,120
I wouldn't say that.

58
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,520
The more of a crisis he's in,

59
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,200
the less he wants his family to be affected.

60
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,880
If you truly care for your father,

61
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,760
I think the first thing you should consider is

62
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,440
how to successfully finish your college degree.

63
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,240
Right.

64
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,720
Yin Zixi.

65
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:39,760
Remember,

66
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,930
never reveal your identity at school.

67
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,000
During this sensitive debt period,

68
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,130
the school will also keep your secret.

69
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,120
Why can't I find it anywhere?

70
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:53,200
Is it really such a wealthy group?

71
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,560
Yeah.

72
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,000
With just one project,

73
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,400
they can shake all the media in Xihai City.

74
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:01,760
If it's such a wealthy group,

75
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:04,240
it's possible that you can't find them.

76
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:04,920
Huh?

77
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,240
Like the Rothschild family in America,

78
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,160
they've been behind the scenes,

79
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,960
controlling the world economy for over 200 years.

80
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,970
Never heard of them.

81
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,880
Of course.

82
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,480
The richer they are, the more mysterious they get.

83
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,279
Why?

84
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,240
Because everyone who had contact with them vanished,

85
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,360
so outsiders wouldn't know of their existence.

86
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,640
Just kidding.

87
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,600
Oh.

88
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,200
A group that can shock Xihai City

89
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,360
shouldn't be impossible to find online.

90
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:40,159
Did you remember the name wrong?

91
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:41,920
No.

92
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,680
I didn't get it wrong.

93
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,600
Dear Mr. An,

94
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,500
Sorry to keep you waiting.

95
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,080
This is your student ID, right?

96
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,480
How did he get it?

97
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,760
This is terrible.

98
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,960
So Mr. An has it.

99
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,920
No wonder.

100
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,680
How do you know about me and An'ers Group?

101
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,340
What's so strange about that?

102
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,040
The Yin family is also a noble family.

103
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,240
We know a bit more than ordinary people.

104
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,200
That's normal.

105
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,720
Never heard of it.

106
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,160
Then let me tell you.

107
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,080
Our Yin family

108
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,080
is closely related to the Rothschild family in the US.

109
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,400
This secret,

110
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,440
is now only known to you.

111
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,800
Oh.

112
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:43,120
Since we've both put our cards on the table,

113
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,400
if there's nothing else,

114
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,330
I'll be leaving.

115
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,200
Since you are already here, Miss Yin,

116
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,640
leaving without making a deal...

117
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,970
Are you feeling guilty?

118
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,440
Of course not.

119
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,640
It's just...

120
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:58,600
I don't have a say in my family's affairs,

121
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,640
so I probably can't make any deals.

122
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,320
Take a look first.

123
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,560
As long as I don't tell anyone?

124
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,560
It's that simple?

125
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,610
I can tutor you in another subject.

126
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:24,920
The penalty for breach of contract is only 50,000.

127
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,280
I can add two more zeros.

128
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,800
Fifty thousand it is.

129
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:32,840
Our big family doesn't sweat the small stuff.

130
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,240
Did you find it?

131
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,640
But the other party needs

132
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:55,720
this amount.

133
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:58,040
Five thousand.

134
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,980
Money is not a problem.

135
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,610
As long as it's guaranteed.

136
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:03,650
I handle things.

137
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,480
You can rest assured.

138
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,640
Someone has already come to buy the answers.

139
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,240
Someone is interfering this time.

140
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,720
There aren't many people taking the makeup exam.

141
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,800
Who is so bold?

142
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,780
It doesn't matter.

143
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,250
This kind of small money

144
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,690
won't affect anything.

145
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,880
Here, look at this.

146
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,560
Teacher!

147
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,000
The classmates are fighting!

148
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,880
Quick, come with me to take a look.

149
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,240
Why are they fighting again?

150
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,360
Didn't they just fight a couple of days ago?

151
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,820
Let's go take a look first.

152
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,200
Oh, let's go.

153
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,640
Mass Communication Theory,

154
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:01,320
Introduction to Journalistic Psychology,

155
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,920
Explanation of Past Papers,

156
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,600
Notes.

157
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:08,200
Looks like your disguise went smoothly.

158
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,080
Sigh.

159
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,760
The other party saw through it a long time ago.

160
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,600
Really?

161
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,320
Yeah.

162
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,520
The agreement only says fifty thousand.

163
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:15,240
Isn't it because he saw

164
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,970
that I'm an ordinary student who can't afford it?

165
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,480
This is trouble.

166
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,400
What's wrong?

167
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,760
Tell me,

168
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:24,240
why would he tutor you

169
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,040
for no reason?

170
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,840
He wants me to keep his secret.

171
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:29,320
No.

172
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,370
Only dead people can keep secrets.

173
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:35,690
Have you finished reading your novel?

174
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,600
I'm serious.

175
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,039
Let me tell you,

176
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,200
even the richest families

177
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,159
always hire a lot of servants, right?

178
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:45,090
How could they hide it completely?

179
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,760
This tutoring is him screening you,

180
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,890
testing whether you can keep a secret.

181
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,040
Maybe

182
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,360
he is somewhere right now

183
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,800
monitoring us.

184
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,680
Ah.

185
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,280
These are the test answers.

186
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:17,920
No.

187
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:21,560
This is a trial given to you by the Rothschild family.

188
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,080
Ha.

189
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,720
Casting Director Xi Chongjing,

190
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,640
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao,

191
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,600
Grip Truck Yi Mingle,

192
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,560
Yi Tong.
